he most massive S0 and Sa galaxies. Our\nresults challenge the idea that galaxies at fixed mass form a homogeneous\npopulation with small scatter in their properties. Instead we find that massive\ngalaxies form a highly diverse population at z>1, in marked contrast to the\nlocal Universe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Aug 2011 20:00:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 5 Oct 2011 20:33:32 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 15 Oct 2011 12:11:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-30"}
